& [TAxisBoundarySlice] is a project-local inquiry contract
  + [canonical_specification_uuid] is fb7480d0-adea-4708-b0ef-336b0e8b3f4d
  + [source_snapshot_uuid] is 386555da-4497-4f6c-a62f-3da7d5fc9ddd
  + [project_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [active_authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [purpose] is compare finite Euler-product and logarithmic-derivative residual behavior along selected t ordinates at fixed sigma values greater than 1
  + [not_purpose] is RH proof, disproof, critical-line inspection, independent zero certification, or theorem-level statement about zero ordinates

  = must: require all sigma values to be greater than 1
  = must: compute zeta(s), finite Euler-product residuals, and logarithmic-derivative residuals for each selected t
  = must: expose t_gap_from_previous and adjacent t transition ratios where possible
  = must: annotate t = 0 as pole_axis_reference when selected
  = must: annotate known zero ordinates as reference landmarks only, not zero certification
  = must: compare behavior at at least one near-boundary sigma and one safer sigma when requested
  = must: mark output proof_status as finite_t_axis_boundary_probe_not_zero_line_evidence
  - never: treat t-axis landmarks as proof of zeros
  - never: infer RH truth or falsehood from finite t-axis residual slices

& [TAxisBoundaryProbeTool] is the script surface for the bridge
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\t_axis_boundary_probe.py
  + [runtime_function] is rh_math.euler_product.t_axis_boundary_probe
  + [input] is finite sigma values greater than 1, t values, prime bounds, precision metadata, and reference ordinates
  + [output] is residual rows, t-axis annotations, adjacent-t transition ratios, and summary rows
  + [proof_status] is finite_t_axis_boundary_probe_not_zero_line_evidence

